-- PRESS DIGEST- Financial Times - May 14
-- 
-- Tue May 13, 2014 08:30PM EDT
-- None



May 14 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines  ED BALLS TELLS CHANCELLOR TO CURB HELP TO BUY TO BOOST RECOVERY (http://link.reuters.com/fyn39v)  PFIZER CONCEDES AZ TAKEOVER MEANS CUTS TO JOBS AND R&D (http://link.reuters.com/gyn39v)  WEB GROUPS BRACE FOR FLOOD OF DATA REQUESTS (http://link.reuters.com/hyn39v)  GOLDMAN'S TWITTER BANKER JOINS HEDGE FUND (http://link.reuters.com/jyn39v)  S&P 500 TOUCHES 1,900 FOR FIRST TIME (http://link.reuters.com/myn39v)  Overview  Shadow chancellor Ed Balls said the British government needed to rein in the Help to Buy scheme in London or risked endangering recovery.  U.S. drug maker Pfizer <PFE.N> Chief Executive Ian Read admitted before British lawmakers that a merger with AstraZeneca <AZN.L> would mean job losses and reduced research spending.  U.S. internet giants including Google <GOOGL.O> are preparing for a plethora of requests from European citizens to remove sensitive personal information after a landmark ruling by the European Court of Justice.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> technology investment banker Anthony Noto, who helped orchestrate Twitter's <TWTR.N> IPO last year, is leaving and joining hedge fund Coatue Management.